<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Help</title>
    <link rel="icon" href="/img/cloudy-day.png">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    {{>header}}
    <div class="main-content">
        
        
        <h2>How to Use Cynrise Forecast</h2>
        
        <div class="help-section">
            <h3>Getting Started</h3>
            <p>Simply enter any city name or location in the search box on the homepage and click "Search" to get current weather conditions.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="help-section">
            <h3>What You'll See</h3>
            <p>The app displays the location name, current temperature, weather description, and "feels like" temperature to give you a complete picture of the conditions.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="help-section">
            <h3>Tips</h3>
            <p>• Try searching by city name (e.g., "Boston")</p>
            <p>• Include state for more specific results (e.g., "Portland, Maine")</p>
            <p>• Works for locations worldwide!</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="help-section">
            <h3>Need More Help?</h3>
            <p>This app uses real-time data from WeatherStack and Mapbox APIs to provide accurate weather information.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    {{>footer}}
</body>
</html>